IRS990.MissionDesc: THE GWINNETT TECH FOUNDATION EXISTS FOR THE SOLE PURPOSE OF HELPING GWINNETT TECHICAL COLLEGE AND ITS STUDENTS SUCCEED THROUGH FINANCIAL SUPPORT INCLUDING SCHOLARSHIPS.
IRS990.Desc: THE FOUNDATION'S EXEMPT PURPOSE IS TO GENERATE AND PROVIDE ADDITIONAL FUNDS FOR THE SUPPORT OF THE STUDENTS, PROGRAMS AND SERVICES OF GWINNETT TECHNICAL COLLEGE IN ORDER TO HELP THE COLLEGE ACHIEVE ITS STATED GOALS AND OBJECTIVES. GWINNETT TECH IS A TWO-YEAR TECHNICAL COLLEGE THAT HAS OVER 21,000 STUDENTS.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: SCHEDULE D, PART XI, LINE 2B & PART XII, LINE 2A:
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: DONATED SERVICES: GWINNETT TECH FOUNDATION DOES NOT HAVE ANY EMPLOYEES. ALL INDIVIDUALS WHO MANAGE AND PERFORM THE DAY-TO-DAY OPERATIONAL WORK OF THE FOUNDATION ARE EMPLOYED BY AND PAID BY GWINNETT TECHNICAL COLLEGE, AN UNRELATED ORGANIZATION. ALL COMPENASION DECISIONS ARE HANDLED BY GWINNETT TECHINICAL COLLEGE UNDER THE COLLEGE'S COMPENSATION POLICIES AND PROCEDURES. THE FOUNDATION SHOWS A CONTRIBUTION FROM THE COLLEGE OF "DONATED SERVICES" ON SCHEDULE D AND A CORRESPONDING EXPENSE RELATED TO THESE "DONATED SERVICES" ALSO ON SCHEDULE D.

RecipientTable.PurposeOfGrantTxt: BOTH THE CASH AND NON-CASH GRANTS SUPPORT THE ACADEMIC PURSUITS OF GWINNETT TECHNICAL COLLEGE
208 NEED & MERIT BASED SCHOLARSHIPS APPROVED BY AND FOR THE STUDENTS OF GWINNETT TECHNICAL COLLEGE

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: ALL GRANTS AND SCHOLARSHIP PAYMENTS ARE MADE TO GWINNETT TECHNICAL COLLEGE. THE COLLEGE MUST REQUEST FUNDS FOR DISBURSEMENT WHETHER FOR EDUCATIONAL MATERIALS OR SCHOLARSHIPS BY STATING THE PURPOSE AND USE BY THE COLLEGE. ALL GIFT-IN-KIND DONATIONS ARE PROCESSED BY THE FOUNDATION AND THEN TRANSFERRED DIRECTLY TO THE COLLEGE. SCHOLARSHIPS TO STUDENTS OF GWINNETT TECHNICAL COLLEGE ARE REQUESTED BY THE COLLEGE, AND THE FOUNDATION DOES NOT MAKE ANY RECOMMENDATIONS OR DETERMINATION WITH RESPECT TO THE SCHOLARSHIP RECIPIENTS. THE FOUNDATION HAS ACCESS TO THE COLLEGE'S RECORDS TO VALIDATE THE USE OF THE FUNDS.

THE GWINNETT TECH FOUNDATION DOES NOT HAVE ANY EMPLOYEES. THE EXECUTIVE DIRECTOR AND ALL OTHER PERSONNEL ARE EMPLOYEES OF GWINNETT TECHNICAL COLLEGE, AN UNRELATED ORGNIZATION, WHICH DONATES THEIR SERVICES TO THE FOUNDATION: MARY BETH BYERLY, EXECUTIVE DIRECTOR $42,820 OF HER W-2 SALARY (40%) AND $14,219 OF HER BENEFITS (40%) ARE ATTRIBUTABLE TO SERVICES RENDERED TO THE FOUNDATION

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION A, LINE 2
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE BOARD OF TRUSTEES IS COMPOSED OF BUSINESS, GOVERNMENT, AND COMMUNITY LEADERS IN THE LOCAL AREA. DUE TO THE EXTENSIVE INVOLVEMENT OF THESE COMMUNITY LEADERS IN BUSINESS AND OTHER COMMUNTY AFFAIRS, THE TRUSTEES MAY HAVE NORMAL BUSINESS RELATIONSHIPS THAT MIGHT BE EXPECTED OF LEADERS IN A SUBURBAN COMMUNITY. HOWEVER, THESE BUSINESS RELATIONSHIPS SHALL BE CONDUCTED AT ARMS' LENGTH, PURSUANT TO NORMAL BUSINESS TERMS AND THE FOUNDATION'S CONFLICT OF INTEREST POLICY.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 11B
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE FORM 990 IS REVIEWED BY THE FINANCE COMMITTEE AND THEN PRESENTED TO THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS FOR THEIR REVIEW AND APPROVAL BEFORE FILING.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 12C
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE CONFLICT OF INTEREST POLICY IS ACKNOWLEDGED AND SIGNED WHEN A OFFICER OR TRUSTEE BEGINS THEIR POSITION WITH THE FOUNDATION. MONITORING IS ACHIEVED THROUGH THE POLICY'S REQUIREMENT TO BRING TO THE ATTENTION OF THE BOARD OR THE EXECUTIVE COMMITTEE ANY AND ALL BUSINESS OR OTHER RELATIONSHIPS THAT COME UNDER THE PURVIEW OF THE POLICY.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION C, LINE 18
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE FOUNDATION MAKES ITS EXEMPT STATUS DETERMINATION LETTER AVAILABLE UPON REQUEST TO THE PUBLIC ALONG WITH ITS FORM 990 RETURNS WHICH ARE ALSO AVAILABLE ON ITS WEBSITE.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION C, LINE 19
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE FOUNDATION'S GOVERNING DOCUMENTS, CONFLICT OF INTEREST POLICY AND FINANCIAL STATEMENTS ARE AVAILABLE UPON REQUEST AND ON THE FOUNDATION'S WEBSITE.
THE METHOD BY WHICH THE FOUNDATION CHOOSES AN AUDITOR AND REVIEWS ITS FINANCIAL STATMENTS HAS NOT CHANGED SINCE THE PRIOR YEAR.
